if they were to be complied with , the large countries &apos; demands for increased power in the Council and Parliament would upset the whole balance within the EU and mean that the small countries would have to pay for the whole cost of enlargement .
a Union of this kind would be centralised in character and give the small countries less influence than that which the United States &apos; s two-chamber system gives to small federal states .
